  "body": "Hi,\r\nI am having a issue with using a uniswap library (https://github.com/Uniswap/smart-order-router) on a forked Hardhat node. \r\n\r\nThe library executes several `eth_call`s, some of which exceed the default gas limit per `eth_call` on most nodes.\r\n\r\nIt is possible with Geth/Erigon to update this limit by using the RPC call `--rpc.gascap {LIMIT}`. When I call my node directly after increasing the limit, it works. However, when I fork from the node with Hardhat, the calls will fail with:\r\n\r\n```\r\n  TransactionExecutionError: Transaction ran out of gas\r\n      at HardhatNode._manageErrors (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:1928:14)\r\n      at HardhatNode._gatherTraces (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:1652:30)\r\n      at async HardhatNode.runCall (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/node.ts:615:20)\r\n      at async EthModule._callAction (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/modules/eth.ts:353:9)\r\n      at async HardhatNetworkProvider._sendWithLogging (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:139:22)\r\n      at async HardhatNetworkProvider.request (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/provider/provider.ts:116:18)\r\n      at async JsonRpcHandler._handleRequest (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/jsonrpc/handler.ts:188:20)\r\n      at async JsonRpcHandler._handleSingleRequest (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/jsonrpc/handler.ts:167:17)\r\n      at async Server.JsonRpcHandler.handleHttp (project/node_modules/hardhat/src/internal/hardhat-network/jsonrpc/handler.ts:52:21)\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs it possible to do update the limit in Hardhat forking mode? Nothing that I've tried has seemed to work.\r\nThanks \r\n",
