    "body": "If you don't specify a `gasLimit` value, then `eth_call` will use the block gas limit (or a close value) as its gas limit. For example, if I deploy a contract with a function like this:\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n    function gasLeft() public view {\r\n      console.log(gasleft());\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\nand then I call that method after setting different `blockGasLimit` values, the logged number changes accordingly. So in principle changing the block gas limit should help if you don't want to manually set a `gasLimit` for all your calls.\r\n\r\nI'm not really sure how I can help here. If you create a minimal reproduction example of the problem you're having, I will take a deeper look.",
